commentTextItems.html: that's it, it's all over, Hussey plays a half-pull, half-hook to the boundary ... Australia take a 3-0 lead and they won this game at a canter

commentPostTextItems.html: England huffed and puffed to 228, a total achieved only after their lower order rallied and scored useful runs late in the innings. All of Australia's bowlers took wickets.

Australia, on the other hand, were slow at the start but they didn't lose wickets and moved steadily towards their goal. White's century was supremely compiled and Clarke made a valuable half-century. It was the first successful chase of the series. Australia lead 3-0 with four matches to play. The next game is at Lord's on September 12.
I hope you've enjoyed our coverage today, on behalf of Will Luke, this is George Binoy signing off. That's all folks.

commentTextItems.html: Hussey jumps down the track and chips the ball high in the air over wide mid-on, there's no one there and the ball bounces and rolls slowly towards the boundary, it doesn't get there but the batsmen run four!

commentPreTextItems.html: Australia need 8 off the last two overs, Anderson will bowl the penultimate one.

commentTextItems.html: Ferguson jumps down the track and dabs to the off side, the batsmen hesitate but then decide to take on the fielder, Bopara misses at the bowler's end with Ferguson at least a foot short
Hussey plays and misses, he was no where close to making contact

commentTextItems.html: Ferguson latches on to the width outside off and cuts hard behind point for another four
sliding down leg again and White flicks firmly towards deep midwicket
Bresnan digs it in short but it's slanting down leg side, no wide called though
there's an appeal for lbw but it's missing leg stump, the batsmen run a leg bye
wide ball outside off stump, poor stuff from Bresnan and Ferguson cashes in, he frees his arms and cuts the ball through the gap at cover point
full toss and it gets driven straight past the bowler for one

stories.title: Australia eye 7-0 whitewash over sleepy England
stories.subTitle: England v Australia, 3rd ODI, The Rose Bowl
stories.seoTitle: Australia eye 7-0 whitewash over sleepy England
stories.summary: This was just another day, just another defeat, for a team of cricketers going through the motions as the summer winds to a close. But Australia are eyeing an unthinkable 7-0 whitewash
stories.byline: Andrew Miller at The Rose Bowl

image.caption: Cameron White drives off the back foot

stories.title: Sparkling White ton flattens England
stories.subTitle: England v Australia, 3rd ODI, The Rose Bowl
stories.summary: Cameron White scored his maiden international hundred, and Michael Clarke signed off as captain with a sheet-anchor 52 from 92 balls, as Australia took a 3-0 lead in the seven-match ODI series
stories.byline: The Bulletin by Andrew Miller at The Rose Bowl
